headline: How Investors May Respond To Garmin (GRMN) Expanding HSA/FSA Eligibility and Launching New Aviator Smartwatches
summary: In October 2025, Garmin announced a partnership with Truemed, allowing eligible U.S. customers to use pre-tax HSA/FSA funds for reimbursement of select smartwatches, fitness trackers, and cycling products, and also launched the D2 Air X15 and D2 Mach 2 aviator smartwatches featuring advanced aviation functionalities. This collaboration may increase financial accessibility for health-focused buyers, while the new aviation wearable launches further broaden Garmin's reach in specialized...
